name: SVGPathElement
description: The SVGPathElement interface corresponds to the <path> element.

members.name: SVGPathElement.pathLength
members.description: An SVGAnimatedNumber corresponding to the pathLength attribute of the given <path> element. Note: In SVG 2 this property was moved to the SVGGeometryElement interface, from which this interface inherits it.

members.name: SVGPathElement.getTotalLength()
members.description: Returns a float representing the computed value for the total length of the path using the browser's distance-along-a-path algorithm, as a distance in the current user coordinate system. Note: In SVG 2 this method was moved to the SVGGeometryElement interface, from which this interface inherits it.

members.name: SVGPathElement.getPointAtLength()
members.description: Returns an SVGPoint representing the x and y coordinates in user space utilizing the browser's distance-along-a-path algorithm. Note: In SVG 2 this method was moved to the SVGGeometryElement interface, from which this interface inherits it.

parameters.name: distance
parameters.description: A float referring to the distance along the path.

members.name: SVGPathElement.getPathSegAtLength()
members.description: Returns an unsigned long representing the index within the pathSegList utilizing the user agent's distance-along-a-path algorithm.
